                    For AA, the minimum contrast ratio required is 4.5:1 for regular text and 3:1 for larger or bold text.
                    <br />
                    For AAA, the contrast ratio required is higher, with a minimum of 7:1 for regular text and 4.5:1 for larger or bold text.
                    <br />
                    These contrast ratios help ensure that text on websites is easily readable for all users, including those with visual impairments.
                </p>

                <h2 class="Heading-Color" style="margin-top:35px">IMPORTANT DEFINITIONS</h2>
                <p>In color contrast, "AA" and "AAA" refer to two levels of compliance with the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG), which provide recommendations for making web content more accessible to people with disabilities. Specifically, they relate to the contrast ratio between text and its background.</p>

                <h3 class="Heading-Color">AA</h3>
                <p>
                    This level of compliance requires a minimum contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for normal text and 3:1 for larger text (18pt or larger) or bold text. Meeting this standard ensures that text is reasonably legible for most users.
                </p>

                <h3 class="Heading-Color">AA (18pt)</h3>
                <p>
                    This specifies the contrast requirements specifically for larger text, which must have a minimum contrast ratio of 3:1 to meet the AA standard.
                </p>

                <h3 class="Heading-Color">AAA</h3>
                <p>
                    This is a higher level of compliance, requiring a more stringent contrast ratio of at least 7:1 for normal text and 4.5:1 for larger or bold text. Meeting this standard ensures that text is highly legible for most users, including those with low vision.
                </p>

                <h3 class="Heading-Color">AAA (18pt)</h3>
                <p>
                    Similar to AA (18pt), this specifies the contrast requirements specifically for larger text to meet the AAA standard.
                </p>

